<subSubSection id="B295069A5051286476F97069EBA4CDC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="syn">
<paragraph id="19EE8EB0B96B24B978A495E2A60E4F6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Syn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D052C0D3616EC8B88EF6980AE75602B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C559B2CFFE5F5CB96DF87D9442BA992" authorityName="van Jaarsv" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe tongaensis" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tongaensis">
<emphasis id="950D675E8F15D9977E770FFEB1F46E44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe tongaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Van Jaarsv.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E274CA126312350BE40ECEB7A3F153B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="D9AAF26B389A242AA182104821DC671E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6055078D2711250D5EC7E486DA611EBF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Tree, 4-8 m high, with rounded crown. 
<emphasis id="20355008FC3ED80060BAE2B7B6CC358E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Trunk</emphasis>
60-80 cm diameter at base, erect, dichotomously branched, without persistent dried leaves, with grey bark. 
<emphasis id="F12EF34F80D5F84225A2E6989DF1A984" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leaves</emphasis>
rosulate at branch tips, spreading to recurved, dull green, without markings, leathery, ensiform, upper surface canaliculate, 40-59 cm long, 4.5 cm wide; margin with teeth, 2 mm long, 5-10 mm apart. 
<emphasis id="A5BA3F96FA8E09914440A54ED657062F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Inflorescence</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="6370018F3287DB5C01D451F43FC54EF4" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.35 m tall, erect, up to 6-branched. 
<emphasis id="E97FA897E6B5AA413112984C1B137291" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Racemes</emphasis>
capitate, 4-6 cm long, rather dense. 
<emphasis id="D56864988514286D4DBA24D3C282E2F4" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Floral bracts</emphasis>
12-14 mm long, 3-4 mm wide. 
<emphasis id="7A8535E4B825F16F841750492C8E7F0A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pedicels</emphasis>
10-14 mm long. 
<emphasis id="2E15C89A84FB1FD810BB7A2C88EF19CA" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flowers</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="27B261D0ABF4ACD71DCBA889FE808FF9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">perianth</emphasis>
yellowish-orange, 47-50 mm long, 8-9 mm across ovary, narrowing very slightly towards mouth, cylindrical, curved; outer segments free for 10 mm; 
<emphasis id="E4A4AC8853776D13891226148FBB4CAE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">stamens</emphasis>
exserted 3-5 mm; 
<emphasis id="42A1DD0D13340A100F3D34187C882268" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">style</emphasis>
exserted to 7 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="14CA372CA675B14C378F674CD7AE7216" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="flowering time">
<paragraph id="F345350EFBDD28F1A17FE0DBBF0F20F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flowering time.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31594BB3945779F1CC6AFAC25961C83D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mainly April-May.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1BB14E83B0E34733B81B0624F387B14" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="0DC131539E1C33C944EB656BEE1CEFFE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA8E2E7BEFA4824E151FFA9788980B5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sand forest and coastal dune forest, in warm, humid, tropical/subtropical conditions, on sandy soil.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5619DD51F7EE0D7B1F4D50952779F03" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="86A1533A6DC280AB12F59A22EC9BB270" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="995972650EBAB21CB6E4E7341024CE87" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="56FF8E397F9ADD50C75B8F7E9B2C7158" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloidendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloidendron tongaense" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tongaense">
<emphasis id="9B2B8C42591DA53D789039604CE196CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloidendron tongaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of only two large tree aloes indigenous to KwaZulu-Natal. These two aloes both have dichotomously branched stems that lack persistent dried leaves. 
<taxonomicName id="CD02BF603A6D3E01DDA604EE1D7E9A55" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloidendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloidendron tongaense" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tongaense">
<emphasis id="414F29EC81486A7BB61588D5414C762F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloidendron tongaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="DC4607539F1CE99BDCDDB854AEAED964" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloidendron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloidendron barberae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barberae">
<emphasis id="FF007385065D50D96BB047514C0A3233" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloidendron barberae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being a shorter tree (up to 8 m, not up to 18 m) with fewer branches and having smaller dull green leaves of 40-59 cm long (not bright green and 60-90 cm). The inflorescence is also slightly shorter at 
<normalizedToken id="E72BDE8263046FE665A2A2A4C9A24A20" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.35 m (not 0.4-0.6 m) and up to 6-branched (not 3-branched from a single point), with shorter capitate racemes of 4-6 cm long (not cylindrical and 20-30 cm), bearing curved yellowish-orange flowers that are 47-50 mm long (not straight rose-pink flowers of 33-37 mm) with stamens exserted 3-5 mm at anthesis (not up to 15 mm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CC5DEDAA2ADE53E70D84F5A3F2498082" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="BE392102258620BE10A701D9D1B388C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B38B408C8E0B0D809363721C35B8C19" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Least Concern (
<bibRefCitation id="87DED06B20353E58369EE89F888D5BAC" author="Von Staden, L" journalOrPublisher="Aloe" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://redlist.sanbi.org" refId="B59" refString="Von Staden, L, Nichols, G, Grieve, G, 2013. Aloidendrontongaense (Van Jaarsv.) Klopper &amp; Gideon F.Sm. National Assessment: Red List of South African Plants version 2017.1. http://redlist.sanbi.org" title="Aloidendrontongaense (Van Jaarsv.) Klopper &amp; Gideon F. Sm. National Assessment: Red List of South African Plants version 2017.1." url="http://redlist.sanbi.org" year="2013">Von Staden et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50DCD2AE15AD5F9FE1384BCB476D080C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7056129BDE96FCE66DF240C99AA8E120" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="407FC8A17B7B7D2740749556D22B8821" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Occurs in the sand forest and coastal dune forest at Kosi Bay in northern KwaZulu-Natal (Maputaland), South Africa and along the southern Mozambique coast as far north as Inhambane, with a known disjunct collection further north in the Cheringoma District of east-central Mozambique (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E65AE0B77987BD6ED098C28299906F4B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Aloidendron tongaense. Photo: N. R. Crouch." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.142.48365.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/388230" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
). It is a near-endemic of the Maputaland Centre of Endemism (
<bibRefCitation id="958F44AC8319E10D525632AC5D391255" author="Van Wyk, AE" journalOrPublisher="Aloe" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B55" refString="Van Wyk, AE, Smith, GF, 2001. Regions of Floristic Endemism in Southern Africa. A Review with Emphasis on Succulents. Umdaus Press, Hatfield, Pretoria." title="Regions of Floristic Endemism in Southern Africa. A Review with Emphasis on Succulents. Umdaus Press, Hatfield, Pretoria." year="2001">Van Wyk and Smith 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACAFC8E97590AC56518F928E3341CA05" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7F487014A2A2E6BDAD4E8D38C1C15C57" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11AF2B209BD8349D706C98479814520F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This aloe was previously considered to be a coastal form of 
<taxonomicName id="4B6A67A74266EAFF37D88EAE803CB77E" genus="A." lsidName="A. barberae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="barberae">
<emphasis id="006594A666F6F3FC1FB222D1B509A9BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. barberae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but was later accorded species status (
<bibRefCitation id="186B1E9BFFA8AD9DE1C7681D3200A4CD" author="Van Jaarsveld, EJ" journalOrPublisher="Aloe" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="64 - 71" refId="B51" refString="Van Jaarsveld, EJ, 2010. Aloe tongaensis, a new species from Tongaland, KwaZulu-Natal (South Africa), and a new sectional arrangement of the tree aloes. Aloe 47: 64 - 71" title="Aloe tongaensis, a new species from Tongaland, KwaZulu-Natal (South Africa), and a new sectional arrangement of the tree aloes." volume="47" year="2010">Van Jaarsveld 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Although the protologue and subsequent literature states that the species is only known from northern KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa and adjacent areas of southern Mozambique, herbarium specimens indicate that it occurs much wider in Mozambique. In fact, numerous specimens from lowland parts of Mozambique, previously regarded as 
<taxonomicName id="E197132DFFB494BCCF38A6D872269CDD" genus="A." lsidName="A. barberae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="barberae">
<emphasis id="8D44CEE0ED0D386EED5187BE67D41494" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. barberae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have now been assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="8389E68BFAFA3CD51370E1FA6E39EE70" genus="A." lsidName="A. tongaense" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tongaense">
<emphasis id="CF15D54421C94AB0B848D1633933BADC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. tongaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="264EB788D6843E43FB7A8B46B4E0F702" author="Walker, CC" journalOrPublisher="Bradleya" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B61" refString="Walker, CC, Smith, GF, Figueiredo, E, Klopper, RR, Crouch, NR, Condy, G, 2019b. Aloidendronbarberae. Flowering Plants of Africa 66: 8-21, t.2342." title="Aloidendronbarberae. Flowering Plants of Africa 66: 8 - 21, t. 2342." year="2019 b">Walker et al. 2019b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
